4 Section 2. Section 50-40-103, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "50-40-103. Definitions. As used in this part, the following definitions apply:
6 (1) (a) "Bar" means an establishment with a license issued pursuant to Title 16, chapter 4, that is
7 devoted to serving alcoholic beverages for consumption by guests or patrons on the premises and in which the
8 serving of food is only incidental to the service of alcoholic beverages or gambling operations. The term
9 includes but is not limited to taverns, night clubs, cocktail lounges, and casinos.
10 (b) The term does not include a cigar bar.
11 (2) "Cigar bar" means an establishment with a license issued pursuant to Title 16, chapter 4, part
12 2, that holds a cigar bar endorsement under [section 1] that permits the smoking of cigars in an enclosed public
13 place.
14 (3) "Department" means the department of public health and human services provided for in 2-15-
15 2201.
16 (4) "Enclosed public place" means an indoor area, room, or vehicle that the general public is
17 allowed to enter or that serves as a place of work, including but not limited to the following:
18 (a) restaurants;
19 (b) stores;
20 (c) public and private office buildings and offices, including all office buildings and offices of
21 political subdivisions, as provided for in 50-40-201, and state government;
22 (d) trains, buses, and other forms of public transportation;
23 (e) health care facilities;
24 (f) auditoriums, arenas, and assembly facilities;
25 (g) meeting rooms open to the public;
26 (h) bars, but not including cigar bars as defined in subsection (2) of this section that meet the
27 requirements of [section 1];
28 (i) community college facilities;
