14 Section 3. Section 50-40-104, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "50-40-104. Smoking in enclosed public places prohibited -- notice to public -- places where
16 prohibition inapplicable. (1) Except as otherwise provided in this section, smoking in an enclosed public place
17 is prohibited.
18 (2) The proprietor or manager of an establishment containing enclosed public places shall post a
19 sign in a conspicuous place at all public entrances to the establishment stating, in a manner that can be easily
20 read and understood, that smoking in the enclosed public place is prohibited.
21 (3) The proprietor or manager of an intrastate bus that is not chartered shall prohibit smoking in all
22 parts of the bus.
23 (4) The prohibition in subsection (1) does not apply to the following places, whether or not the
24 public is allowed access to those places:
25 (a) a private residence unless it is used for any of the following purposes, in which case the
26 prohibition in subsection (1) applies:
27 (i) a family day-care home or group day-care home, as defined in 52-2-703 and licensed pursuant
28 to Title 52, chapter 2, part 7;
